    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIncremental selection doesn't extend if last char is multibyte.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run `nvim --clean test.lua` with the following `test.lua`:\n```lua\nlocal s = 'abc…'\n```\n2. Type `fbvan`, `abc…` is selected.\n3. Continue typing `an`, the selection doesn't extend.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe selection extends at steps 3.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2722+g5a7df03b42\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.46.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR neovim-git",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Using `getregionpos()` seems to solve this specific problem (and also handles exclusive `'selection'`):\n```diff\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_select.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_select.lua\nindex 4fdbf2bd9b..a9a441461a 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_select.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_select.lua\n@@ -375,12 +375,9 @@ end\n \n --- @return Range4\n local function get_selection()\n-  local pos1 = vim.fn.getpos('v')\n-  local pos2 = vim.fn.getpos('.')\n-  if pos1[2] > pos2[2] or (pos1[2] == pos2[2] and pos1[3] > pos2[3]) then\n-    --- @type Range4,Range4\n-    pos1, pos2 = pos2, pos1\n-  end\n+  local r = vim.fn.getregionpos(vim.fn.getpos('v'), vim.fn.getpos('.'), { eol = true })\n+  local pos1 = r[1][1]\n+  local pos2 = r[#r][2]\n   local range = { pos1[2] - 1, pos1[3] - 1, pos2[2] - 1, pos2[3] }\n \n   if range[4] == #vim.fn.getline(range[3] + 1) + 1 then\n```\nBut it seems to cause some other problems.",
